奧羅莫人主要分布在奧羅米亞州，奧羅米亞州是衣索比亞境內根據民族而建立的九個州之一。總面積約為284,538平方公里。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.csa.gov.et/index.php?option=com_rubberdoc&view=doc&id=421&format=raw&Itemid=606 |title=2011 National Statistics |accessdate=2017-05-03 |archive-date=2013-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130330021225/http://www.csa.gov.et/index.php?option=com_rubberdoc&view=doc&id=421&format=raw&Itemid=606 |dead-url=no }}</ref>奧羅米亞州東接[[索馬里州|索馬利亞州]];北部接壤[[阿姆哈拉州|阿姆哈拉州]]，[[阿法尔州|阿法爾州]]和[[本尚古勒-古馬茲州|本尚古勒-古馬茲州]];西接[[南蘇丹|南蘇丹]]，[[甘貝拉州|甘貝拉州]]以及[[南方州|南方州]];南接[[肯亞|肯亞]]。奧羅米亞州位於[[衣索比亞高原|衣索比亞高原]]上，氣候類型是[[熱帶季風氣候|熱帶季風氣候]]，奧羅米亞州所處海拔約為2000公尺左右，由於地勢較高的關係，氣候通常較其他赤道地區涼爽，年平均氣溫18～20℃，四季如春，降水豐富，適宜多種作物生長。奧羅米亞州90％以上的人生活在農村，通常從事小農戶工作。咖啡是該地區主要的經濟作物，是衣索比亞咖啡產量的至少一半。<ref>[https://www.compassion.com/ethiopia/oromia.htm] {{Wayback|url=https://www.compassion.com/ethiopia/oromia.htm |date=20190811092408 }}，Oromia Region.</ref>

==歷史沿革==
===19世紀以前===
[[File:Map_of_Abissinia_(1887).jpg|thumb]]
歷史上，使用阿方奧羅莫語（Afaan Oromoo）的人使用自己的加達制度來治理社會。除此之外，奧羅莫人還有一些與西達馬人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people Sidama People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people |date=20200312014113 }}）共有的獨立王國。包括了吉拉王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gera Kingdom of Gera]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gera |date=20200409005745 }}）、戈瑪王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gomma Kingdom of Gomma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gomma |date=20170320212705 }}）、加羅王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Garo Kingdom of Garo]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Garo |date=20191010113832 }}）、古瑪王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gumma Kingdom of Gumma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gumma |date=20200522230204 }}）、吉瑪王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Jimma Kingdom of Jimma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Jimma |date=20200809134339 }}）、里姆伊那瑞亞王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Limmu-Ennarea Kingdom of Limmu-Ennarea]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Limmu-Ennarea |date=20200409003130 }}）、吉倫王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jiren Jiren]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jiren |date=20170319142443 }}）。

現今所知最早關於奧羅莫人的文獻和詳細的歷史，是由衣索比亞修道士阿拔·巴里（Abba Bahrey）在1593年編撰的Zenahu le Galla，儘管「Gallas」一詞早就在地圖<ref name="Taa2006p18">{{cite book|author=Tesema Ta'a|title=The Political Economy of an African Society in Transformation: the Case of Macca Oromo (Ethiopia)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_XwN2JdMYM4C|year=2006|publisher=Otto Harrassowitz Verlag|isbn=978-3-447-05419-5|pages=17–19 with footnotes}}</ref>或其他地方出現過。<ref name="Pankhurst1997p279">{{cite book|author=Richard Pankhurst|title=The Ethiopian Borderlands: Essays in Regional History from Ancient Times to the End of the 18th Century |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA279 |year=1997|publisher=The Red Sea Press|isbn=978-0-932415-19-6|pages=279–280}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Mohammed Hassen|title=The Oromo and the Christian Kingdom of Ethiopia: 1300-1700 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fg1zCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA222 |year=2015|publisher=Boydell & Brewer|isbn=978-1-84701-117-6|pages=222–225}}</ref>到了十六世紀以後，奧羅莫人更常在歷史上被提及，如：阿拔·波羅斯（Abba Pawlos）、傑歐·伯謬達斯（Joao Bermudes）、吉羅里莫·羅伯（Jerorimo Lobo）、格拉德瓦斯（Galawdewos）、薩爾·登格爾（Sarsa Dengel）等人所記錄關於奧羅莫人的歷史。根據這些記錄所記載，奧羅莫人是集體生活的牧民。這些牧民的畜群開始迅速擴張，因此需要更多的放牧地。在這原因之下，他們開始遷移，但不是集體遷移，而是分群遷移。奧羅莫人並沒有國王，而是根據加達制度來選出名為盧巴（Luba）的領導人。到十六世紀末期，出現了兩個主要的奧羅莫族聯盟：阿弗雷（Afre）聯盟和薩達加（Sadaqa）聯盟。其中阿弗雷聯盟是由四個較老的氏族合併而來，薩達加聯盟則是由三個氏族合併而成。這些奧羅莫族聯盟最初是以衣索比亞南部地區為根據地，但在十六世紀開始往北方遷徙，而被稱為“大奧羅莫遷徙”。<ref name="Pankhurst1997p279"/><ref name="Levine2000p78">{{cite book|author=Donald N. Levine|title=Greater Ethiopia: The Evolution of a Multiethnic Society|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x_mgl0dasR4C |year=2000|publisher=University of Chicago Press|isbn=978-0-226-47561-5|pages=78–89}}</ref><ref name=Degu2002>W.A. Degu, [http://dare.uva.nl/document/66264 "Chapter 7 Political Development in the Pre-colonial Horn of Africa"] {{Wayback|url=http://dare.uva.nl/document/66264 |date=20110724173626 }}, ''The State, the Crisis of State Institutions and Refugee Migration in the Horn of Africa: The Cases of Ethiopia, Sudan and Somalia'', Thela Thesis (Amsterdam, 2002), page 142</ref>

據衣索比亞歷史學家理查德·潘克赫斯特（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Pankhurst_(academic) Richard Pankhurst]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Pankhurst_(academic) |date=20200911220407 }}）敘述，這次遷徙與伊瑪目·艾哈邁德·本·易卜拉欣（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmad_ibn_Ibrahim_al-Ghazi Imam Ahmad ibn Ibrahim]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmad_ibn_Ibrahim_al-Ghazi |date=20210118190732 }}）首次入侵內陸非洲之角相關。<ref name="Pankhurst1997p281">{{cite book|author=Richard Pankhurst|title=The Ethiopian Borderlands: Essays in Regional History from Ancient Times to the End of the 18th Century |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA279 |year=1997|publisher=The Red Sea Press|isbn=978-0-932415-19-6|pages=281–283}}</ref>據歷史學家瑪麗安·巴赫斯吉斯特（Marianne Bechhaus-Gerst）敘述，移民是十五至十六世紀非洲之角地區基督教和穆斯林軍隊之間激烈戰爭的後果之一，造成許多人死亡、人口減少，且可能造成原來的家園乾旱。此外，他們獲得了馬匹，並在加達系統幫助之下協調全副武裝的奧羅莫戰士，使奧羅莫同胞能夠在15世紀20年代開始推進，並到新的地區定居。這種擴張持續到17世紀。<ref name="Shillington2013p1182">{{cite book|author=Marianne Bechhaus-Gerst|editor=Kevin Shillington|title=Encyclopedia of African History |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=umyHqvAErOAC&pg=PA1182 |year=2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-45670-2|pages=1182–1183}}</ref><ref name="Levine2000p78" />

奧羅莫和其他鄰近的種族，如：[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]、西達馬人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people Sidama People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people |date=20200312014113 }}）、阿達爾人和[[索馬里人|索馬利亞人]]的和平融合與暴力競爭影響了奧羅莫人的政治。<ref name="Pankhurst1997p281"/><ref name=Degu2002/>在1500至1800年間，高地基督徒、沿海穆斯林和非洲之角的多神教徒之間出現了一系列戰爭與鬥爭，造成了人口重大的重新分配。
1535年左右，奧羅莫人從南部遷往北部、東部和西部，反映了索馬利亞內陸的大規模擴張。1500至1800年間，[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]的遷徙也影響了衣索比亞的當代民族政治。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hrw.org/reports/pdfs/e/ethiopia/ethiopia.919/c3wollo.pdf |title=Oromo and Amhara rule in Ethiopia |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924181350/http://www.hrw.org/reports/pdfs/e/ethiopia/ethiopia.919/c3wollo.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[索馬里人|索馬利亞人]]從歐加登平原（Ogaden Plain）向西遷移到[[朱巴河|朱巴河]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jubba_River Jubba River]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jubba_River |date=20201127013505 }}），導致與奧羅莫人的衝突。<ref>W.A. Degu, [http://dare.uva.nl/document/66264 "Chapter 7 Political Development in the Pre-colonial Horn of Africa"] {{Wayback|url=http://dare.uva.nl/document/66264 |date=20110724173626 }}, ''The State, the Crisis of State Institutions and Refugee Migration in the Horn of Africa: The Cases of Ethiopia, Sudan and Somalia'', Thela Thesis (Amsterdam, 2002), page 142</ref>這種擴張是索馬利亞人聖戰的一部分，以作為“控制更肥沃土地和擴大伊斯蘭教的手段”，因此，他們設法控制了現今衣索比亞的大部分地區，最遠甚至到了[[厄利垂亞|厄利垂亞]]與紅海交界的沿岸。這些地緣政治發展造成了奧羅莫人與索馬利亞人之間的競爭與衝突，並互相爭奪土地和水資源。<ref name=Degu2002/>根據口頭和文學證據，波拉納奧羅莫人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borana_Oromo_people Borana Oromo People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borana_Oromo_people |date=20190725085319 }}）和索馬利亞部族在十七和十八世紀相互殘害，特別是在邊界附近，但也有相對和平時期。<ref>Paul Trevor William Baxter, Jan Hultin, Alessandro Triulzi. [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=xmp2lsKlqx0C&pg=PA123#v=onepage&q=genitals%20ritualized%20trophy&f=false ''Being and Becoming Oromo: Historical and Anthropological Enquiries'] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=xmp2lsKlqx0C&pg=PA123#v=onepage&q=genitals%20ritualized%20trophy&f=false |date=20200821041248 }}. Nordic Africa Institute (1996) pp. 123–124</ref><ref>Aṣma Giyorgis, Bairu Tafla [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=mGcwAQAAIAAJ ''Aṣma Giyorgis and His Work: History of the Gāllā and the Kingdom of Šawā''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=mGcwAQAAIAAJ |date=20200821041622 }}. Franz Steiner Verlag Wiesbaden GmbH (1987) pp. 439 Google Books</ref>

====奴隸====
奧羅莫人與西達馬人是16世紀之前奴隸主要的來源。戰爭、綁架和司法判刑是奧羅莫人變成奴隸的原因。在一些情況下，奧羅莫的牧民會奴役定居者、部分奧羅莫人改信奉伊斯蘭教或基督教，奧羅莫社會之間的關係就會發生嫌隙。據非洲歷史學家魯道夫·瓦爾（Rudolph Ware）的說法，奴隸制已經成為非洲之角政治經濟中的核心，奧羅莫人沒有選擇。<ref>Young female Galla slaves served as concubines and household workers,{{cite book|author=Bernard Lewis|title=Race and Slavery in the Middle East: An Historical Enquiry|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WdjvedBeMHYC&pg=PA74 |year=1992|publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-505326-5|pages=74–75}}</ref>奴隸制歷史學家保羅·愛洛維奇（Paul E. Lovejoy）認為，“在1600年之前，奴隸制是北方大草原、衣索比亞和東非海岸幾個世紀以來的社會、政治和經濟秩序的基礎”。<ref name="Lovejoy2011p24">{{cite book|author=Paul E. Lovejoy|title=Transformations in Slavery: A History of Slavery in Africa |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dXVFnHqhLvcC&pg=PA24 |year=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-1-139-50277-1|pages=24–25}}</ref>

奴隸被[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]分為兩個群體，一個是「紅色」，且膚色較白；另一為「黑色」，也被稱為巴里亞（Bareya）或山卡拉（Shanqalla），說班圖語而且膚色較深。<ref name=ware2011p72/><ref>{{cite book|author1=Gérard Prunier|author2 =Éloi Ficquet| title=Understanding Contemporary Ethiopia: Monarchy, Revolution and the Legacy of Meles Zenawi|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=wnxeCwAAQBAJ&pg=PT51 |year=2015|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-1-84904-618-3|page=51}}</ref><ref name="Willis2005p122"/>「紅色」奴隸較為昂貴且出口至外地，而「黑色」奴隸則在國內利用，如[[哈比沙人|哈比沙人]]。<ref name=ware2011p72>{{cite book |author = Rudolph T. Ware|editor1=David Eltis|editor2=Stanley L. Engerman|title=The Cambridge World History of Slavery: Volume 3, AD 1420–AD 1804|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3tiaBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA72 |year=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-316-18435-6|pages=72–74}}</ref><ref name="Lovejoy2011p149">{{cite book|author=Paul E. Lovejoy|title=Transformations in Slavery: A History of Slavery in Africa |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dXVFnHqhLvcC&pg=PA149 |year=2011|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-139-50277-1|pages=149–150}}</ref>說庫西特語的奧羅莫奴隸價格較貴，並出口至阿拉伯半島、波斯灣地區、<ref>{{cite book|author=Benjamin Reilly|title=Slavery, Agriculture, and Malaria in the Arabian Peninsula |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jULNCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT116 |year=2015|publisher=Ohio University Press|isbn=978-0-8214-4540-2|pages=116–117}}</ref><ref name="Willis2005p128">{{cite book|author=John Ralph Willis|title=Slaves and Slavery in Africa: Volume Two: The Servile Estate|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HVGRAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA128|year=2005|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-78016-6|pages=128–134|access-date=2017-05-08|archive-date=2020-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214143433/https://books.google.com/books?id=HVGRAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA128|dead-url=no}}</ref>奧圖曼王國<ref>{{cite book|author=Ehud R. Toledano|title=The Ottoman Slave Trade and Its Suppression |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gOH_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA15 |year=2014 |publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-5723-4|pages=15–27}}</ref>和其他地方<ref name=ware2011p72/>。年輕的加拉女性奴隸擔任妾和家庭幫傭，<ref>{{cite book|author=Bernard Lewis|title=Race and Slavery in the Middle East: An Historical Enquiry|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WdjvedBeMHYC&pg=PA74 |year=1992|publisher=Oxford University Press |isbn=978-0-19-505326-5|pages=74–75}}</ref>而男性則主要擔任私人軍隊和奴役勞動力。<ref name="Willis2005p122">{{cite book|author=John Ralph Willis|title=Slaves and Slavery in Africa: Volume Two: The Servile Estate|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XM-PAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA137|year=2005|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-78017-3|pages=122–127, 137}}</ref>

奧羅莫人也同時奴役其他民族。根據百慕達的報導指出，十六世紀奧羅莫人在戰爭中非常兇殘，且殘暴地奴役被他們所征服地區的人民。<ref name=D3-29>Richard Pankhurst [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA284 ''The Ethiopian Borderlands: Essays in Regional History from Ancient Times to the End of the 18th Century''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA284 |date=20200821041859 }}, 1997. p. 284, 423</ref><ref name=D3-3>J. Bermudez [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=b0_uAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA229 ''The Portuguese Expedition to Abyssinia in 1541–1543 as Narrated by Castanhoso''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=b0_uAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA229 |date=20200821035508 }}, 1543. p. 229.</ref>根據阿拔·巴里（Abba Bahrey）的記錄，在伊瑪目·艾哈邁德·本·易卜拉欣（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmad_ibn_Ibrahim_al-Ghazi Imam Ahmad ibn Ibrahim]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmad_ibn_Ibrahim_al-Ghazi |date=20210118190732 }}）的時代，奧羅莫的盧巴部落（Luba Tribe）在達瓦羅（Dawaro）與阿達爾·馬布拉克（Adal Mabraq）進行戰爭，摧毀並佔領了該地區。他們也接管了法塔加（Fatagar）和法伊（Faj），強迫其居民服從奴隸制。<ref name=D3-2-1>Richard Pankhurst [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA284 The Ethiopian Borderlands: Essays in Regional History from Ancient Times to the End of the 18th Century - Google Books"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=zpYBD3bzW1wC&pg=PA284 |date=20200821041859 }}: , 1997. p. 325.</ref><ref name=D3-3/>

[[阿姆哈拉州|阿姆哈拉州]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amhara_Region Amhara Region]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amhara_Region |date=20210125015006 }}）中部是主要的奴隸販賣貿易路線必經之地，<ref>{{cite book|author=Ehud R. Toledano|title=The Ottoman Slave Trade and Its Suppression: 1840-1890|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gOH_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA31 |year=2014|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-5723-4|pages=31–34}}, Quote: "The first section of this [slave] trade was in the hands of Ethiopian dealers who drove the slaves from the southern and southwestern Galla, Sidama and Gurage principalities to the central Amhara provinces. (...) the average Afar caravan consisted of thirty to fifty merchants and about two hundred slaves."</ref>西邊和西南邊接壤[[錫達馬地區|錫達馬地區]]和[[古拉蓋地區|古拉蓋地區]]，延伸到衣索比亞北部和東部。由於奴隸貿易的收入非常有利可圖，吉柏提（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeberti_people Jeberti People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeberti_people |date=20170320212505 }}）、阿法爾（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afar_people Afar]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afar_people |date=20201108174203 }}）、索馬利亞和阿拉伯商人每年出口成千上萬的奴隸。<ref name="Willis2005p128"/><ref name="Lapidus2014p483">{{cite book|author=Ira M. Lapidus|title=A History of Islamic Societies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZkJpBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA483|year=2014|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-139-99150-6|page=483}}</ref>根據中東和伊斯蘭歷史教授伊拉·拉皮度斯（Ira M. Lapidus）介紹，埃塞俄比亞的奴隸貿易使穆斯林受益，並增加了奧羅莫人民的伊斯蘭化。<ref name="Lapidus2014p483"/>

===19世紀===
在十九世紀的頭十年，三個奧羅莫帝國主義者：恩乃亞（Enarya）、戈馬（Goma）和古馬（Guma），逐漸嶄露頭角成為地方巨頭。<ref name=Degu2002/>這些被佔領的地方被稱為加拉地（Galla-Land），包括衣索比亞中部和南部的大部分地區，及現在被其他民族所佔有的土地。<ref>"{{cite EB1911|ref=harv |wstitle=Gallas |volume=Volume 11 |page=414}}</ref>在衣索比亞奧羅莫人民的觀點中，奧羅莫領導人之一的拉斯·戈巴納·達克（Ras Gobana Dacche）帶領衣索比亞往現代化發展，運用政治和軍事力量將更多地區納入衣索比亞的領土。在孟尼利克二世（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menelik_II Menelik II]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Menelik_II |date=20210128203138 }}）的統治下，戈巴納將[[非洲之角|非洲之角]]的許多地區納入了衣索比亞的領土中。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nai.uu.se/library/resources/dossiers/local_history_of_ethiopia/j/ORTJA.pdf |title=Ras Gobena victory against Gurage militia |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305215524/http://www.nai.uu.se/library/resources/dossiers/local_history_of_ethiopia/j/ORTJA.pdf |archive-date=2012-03-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>Donald Levine, ''Greater Ethiopia, the Evolution of a multicultural society'' (University of Chicago Press: 1974)</ref>

奧羅莫人部落之間的關係，以及與第二大族群[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]的關係一直以來都極為複雜，奧羅莫人在部落間的作戰層出不窮。{{Sfn|Donald N. Levine|2014|pp=85, 136}}唐納德·萊文（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_N._Levine Donald N. Levine]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donald_N._Levine |date=20201111201218 }}）敘述，在450年的時間裡，持續到19世紀，[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]與奧羅莫人之間的戰爭「或多或少是連續的」；[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]與奧羅莫人之間的戰爭一直非常具有破壞性。{{Sfn|Donald N. Levine|2014|pp=85-86}}在某些地區，一些奧羅莫人組成了一個聯盟，並與[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]合作。{{Sfn|Donald N. Levine|2014|p=85}}

奧羅莫人與之間的相互關係一直是爭議的議題，有些學者已提出了整合性的證據，然而有些則認為到20世紀都還持續著衝突。從另一個角度來看，經過種族混合的衣索比亞人具有奧羅莫人的背景，所以部分衣索比亞將領和領導人也具有奧羅莫的血統。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd/cstdy:@field(DOCID+et0020) |title=Union of Amhara and Oromo in royal families |publisher=Lcweb2.loc.gov |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06 |archive-date=2013-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318004527/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd%2Fcstdy%3A%40field%28DOCID+et0020%29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>沃洛奧奧羅莫人（[[Wollo_Oromo|Wollo Oromo]]），特別是拉雅奧羅莫人（[[Raya_Oromo|Raya Oromo]]）和葉如奧羅莫人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yejju_Oromo_tribe Yejju Oromo]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yejju_Oromo_tribe |date=20200928111119 }}）是衣索比亞早期逐漸整併時，奧羅莫人中的權力持有者。後來，衣索比亞攸關中央政權的南北運動導致了在西瓦（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa Shewa]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa |date=20210131165348 }}）的奧羅莫人和[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]獲得共治衣索比亞的權力。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd/cstdy:@field(DOCID+et0020) |title=Oromo in Ethiopian leadership |publisher=Lcweb2.loc.gov |date= |accessdate=2017-05-06 |archive-date=2013-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318004527/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd%2Fcstdy%3A%40field%28DOCID+et0020%29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

====更多人淪為奴隸====
[[File:Slaves_in_Ethiopia_-_19th_century.jpg|thumb]]

許多地方對於衣索比亞奴隸的需求，如：阿拉伯、波斯灣、埃及、[[奧圖曼帝國|奧圖曼帝國]]與其他地方，在19世紀上半葉遠遠超過了供應量，導致諸如吉柏提（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeberti_people Jeberti]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeberti_people |date=20170320212505 }}）商人進入衣索比亞深處尋找奴隸。<ref>{{cite book|author=John Ralph Willis|title=Slaves and Slavery in Africa: Volume Two: The Servile Estate |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XM-PAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA126 |year=2005|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-78017-3|page=126}}</ref><ref name="T">{{cite book|author=E. R. Toledano|title=The Ottoman Slave Trade and Its Suppression: 1840-1890 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gOH_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA15 |year=2014|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-1-4008-5723-4|pages=15–16, 21–22, 24–31}}</ref>根據衣索比亞歷史學家理察·潘克赫斯特（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Pankhurst_(academic) Richard Pankhurst]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Pankhurst_(academic) |date=20200911220407 }}）敘述，
從衣索比亞許多地區到紅海、[[亞丁灣|亞丁灣]]、蘇丹和埃及等，19世紀初廣泛奴隸販賣來源很大一部分皆來自奧羅莫地區。<ref>Richard Pankhurst (1976), stable/40758604 The Beginnings of Oromo Studies in ''Africa: Rivista trimestrale di studi e documentazione dell'Istituto italiano per l'Africa e l'Oriente'', Anno 31, No. 2 (GIUGNO 1976), pp. 171-172]</ref>在十九世紀下半葉，稱為哈巴什（Habash）的衣索比亞奴隸在阿拉伯和中東市場仍保持著高度的需求，以作為商人和統治者的僕人、會計、保鏢或妻妾。<ref name=A1-2/><ref name=A1-3/>這些奴隸主要來自奧羅莫和[[錫達馬地區|錫達馬地區]]，<ref name=A1-2>{{cite book|author= Abdussamad Ahmad| editor= William Gervase Clarence-Smith|title=The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IsNcAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA93| year=2013|publisher= Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-18214-4|pages=93–99}}</ref><ref name=A1-3 />他們從[[吉馬|吉馬]]、巴索（[[Basso|Basso]]）等地的奴隸市場被帶走，用大篷車一次將數以千計的人送到了紅海的馬塔馬（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metemma Metemma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metemma |date=20201112040925 }}）、[[马萨瓦|馬薩瓦]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massawa Massawa]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massawa |date=20201129000251 }}）和塔胡拉港（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadjoura Tadjoura]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadjoura |date=20200602051858 }}）。<ref name=A1-2/>

十九世紀初，位於古杜魯（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guduru,_Ethiopia Guduru]）的阿散答波（[[Asandabo|Asandabo]]）、位於里姆伊那瑞亞王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Limmu-Ennarea Kingdom of Limmu-Ennarea]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Limmu-Ennarea |date=20200409003130 }}）的薩加（[[Saqa|Saqa]]）、位於[[吉馬|吉馬]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma Jimma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma |date=20201126123925 }}）的馬塔（[[Hermata|Hermata]]）和位於勒加-納匡特王國（[[Leqa-Naqamte|Leqa-Naqamte]]）的碧羅（[[Billo|Billo]]）是長久以來奴隸商和當地商人會面的主要奴隸市場。<ref name=A1-2-1>W. G. Clarence-Smith [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA108#v=onepage&q=%22asandabo%2C%20saqa%2C%20hermata%20and%20bonga%22&f=false The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Century] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA108#v=onepage&q=%22asandabo%2C%20saqa%2C%20hermata%20and%20bonga%22&f=false |date=20200821035634 }}. Psychology Press (1989) pp. 108 and 93 Google Books</ref><ref name=A22-1>W. G. Clarence-Smith [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA106#v=onepage&q=Bagibo&f=false The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Centuryy] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA106#v=onepage&q=Bagibo&f=false |date=20200821043955 }}. Psychology Press (1989) pp. 106-115 Google Books</ref>這些地區的奴隸交易是收入的主要來源。南部這些主要市場附近的商業村莊總是充滿了奴隸，上層階級為他們所渴望的進口貨物交換了這些奴隸；<ref name=A2-1>Harold G. Marcus [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=jX7-0ROBfyIC&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q=%22The%20Merchant%20villages%20adjacent%20to%20the%20major%20markets%22&f=false A History of Ethiopia] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=jX7-0ROBfyIC&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q=%22The%20Merchant%20villages%20adjacent%20to%20the%20major%20markets%22&f=false |date=20200821041649 }}. University of California Press (1994) pp. 55 Google Books</ref>許多人被其他人遭到突擊搜查，<ref name=A2>Harold G. Marcus [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=jX7-0ROBfyIC&pg=PA55 A History of Ethiopia] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=jX7-0ROBfyIC&pg=PA55 |date=20200821041649 }}. University of California Press (1994) pp. 55 Google Books</ref>奧羅莫人還會抓其他奧羅莫人當作奴隸來販賣；{{Sfn|Donald N. Levine|2014|p=156, According to Levine, this was a large part of the increased slave trade in the first half of the nineteenth century.}}有時奧羅莫人因為微小的過錯而被判處奴隸制，如：欠稅，<ref name=A26>{{cite book|author=G.W.B. Huntingford|title=The Galla of Ethiopia, Ethnographic Survey of Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xHtRAQAAIAAJ|year=1969|publisher=International African Institute (Republished: Routledge)|isbn=978-1138232174|pages=31, 126}}</ref>而被奧羅莫和錫達馬統治者出售。<ref>{{cite book|author=Harold G. Marcus|title=A History of Ethiopia |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jX7-0ROBfyIC&pg=PA55 |year=1994|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=978-0-520-08121-5|pages=55–56}}</ref><ref name=A1-3/><ref name=A24-1>{{cite book|author1=Gwyn Campbell|author2=Suzanne Miers|author3=Joseph Calder Miller|title=Women and Slavery: Africa, the Indian Ocean world, and the medieval north Atlantic |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jgm69dJt4DcC |year=2007|publisher=Ohio University Press|isbn=978-0-8214-1723-2|pages=215–228}}</ref>來自南方這些主要市場的奴隸向北輸往大型分銷市場，如戈賈姆地區（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gojjam Gojjam]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gojjam |date=20210131165347 }}）的巴索（[[Basso|Basso]]），西瓦地區（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa Shewa]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa |date=20210131165348 }}）的[[阿利尤安巴|阿利尤安巴]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aliyu_Amba Aliyu Amba]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aliyu_Amba |date=20160811112116 }}）和阿巴杜雷索（[[Abdul_Resul|Abdul Resul]]），在奴隸出口之前，這些地區對交易徵稅。<ref name=A2 /><ref name=A1-2/>
[[File:Christian_missions_and_social_progress;_a_sociological_study_of_foreign_missions_(1897)_(14783598585).jpg|thumb]]
位於沿海和邊界城鎮，如[[马萨瓦|馬薩瓦]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massawa Massawa]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massawa |date=20201129000251 }}）、塔胡拉（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadjoura Tadjoura]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadjoura |date=20200602051858 }}）和馬塔馬（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metemma Metemma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metemma |date=20201112040925 }}），或是如[[貢德爾|貢德爾]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondar Gondar]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondar |date=20210125135841 }}）和德巴克（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debarq Debarq]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Debarq |date=20201112041708 }}）等商業中心，都會有官員對每個奴隸徵稅，稱之為「Nagadras」。<ref name=A1-2/>一個對於奴隸運輸的研究指出，每年從衣索比亞北部出口的奴隸每年出口超過3300人，而南部每年出口4200多位奴隸。<ref name=A1-3/>記錄中顯示，平均來說，衣索比亞南部地區每年產出15000名新奴隸，包括了奧羅莫人和西達馬人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people Sidama People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sidama_people |date=20200312014113 }}）居住的地區。其中，光是吉馬地區（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma Jimma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma |date=20201126123925 }}）每年出口4000位奴隸，奴隸貿易是該地最具價值的出口項目；<ref name=A1-3-1>W. G. Clarence-Smith [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=IsNcAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA93#v=onepage&q=%22the%20largest%20export%20item%22&f=false The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Centuryy] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=IsNcAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA93#v=onepage&q=%22the%20largest%20export%20item%22&f=false |date=20200821041800 }}. Psychology Press (1989) pp. 93 Google Books</ref>而戈賈姆地區（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gojjam Gojjam]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gojjam |date=20210131165347 }}）則產出了7000位奴隸。<ref name=A1-3>{{cite book|author= Timothy Fernyhough| editor= William Gervase Clarence-Smith|title=The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Century| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IsNcAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA103| year=2013|publisher= Routledge|isbn= 978-1-135-18214-4 |pages= 103–106, 108–112, see Table 2 e.g.}}</ref><ref name=A2 />

據人類學家法蘭謝絲娜·迪克里奇（Francesca Declich）所述，在19世紀和20世紀初期，索馬利亞的市場裡，販賣奴隸的活動一直處於蓬勃發展的盛況，包括[[謝貝利河|謝貝利河]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebelle_River Shebelle River]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shebelle_River |date=20201127012211 }}）周圍的農業地區以及都市和牧區。這些奧羅莫人奴隸在他們所居住的地區被綁架，在襲擊中被捕，或被劫持而成為俘虜。<ref>{{cite journal | last=Declich | first=Francesca | title=Dynamics of Intermingling Gender and Slavery in Somalia at the Turn of the Twentieth Century | journal=Northeast African Studies | publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press | volume=10 | issue=3 | year=2009 | pages=46, 45–69 | doi=10.1353/nas.0.0024 | url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/262476 | accessdate=2017-05-10 | archive-date=2018-06-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602000033/http://muse.jhu.edu/article/262476 | dead-url=no }}</ref>根據對於索馬利亞的市場所做的記錄，如位於[[摩加迪休|摩加迪休]]的市場，奴隸的最高價格為年齡介於15-20歲的“加拉女人”，他們被當作妾來販賣，而主要負責家庭工作的加拉青少年奴隸和8-10歲女孩則以較低的價格在市場上販賣。<ref>{{cite journal | last=Declich | first=Francesca | title=Dynamics of Intermingling Gender and Slavery in Somalia at the Turn of the Twentieth Century | journal=Northeast African Studies | publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press | volume=10 | issue=3 | year=2009 | pages=54, 62–64 | doi=10.1353/nas.0.0024 | url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/262476 | accessdate=2017-05-10 | archive-date=2018-06-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602000033/http://muse.jhu.edu/article/262476 | dead-url=no }}; Note: Declich mentions that Oromo were not only one enslaved and traded in Somali markets, Bantu and Swahili origin women as well were traded as sex slaves and domestic servile work but they attracted lower prices.</ref>

根據殖民地的英國領事館記錄，主要是奧羅莫地區出口奴隸，但衣索比亞的其他地區也出口了奴隸。<ref name=A24-2>R. W. Beachey [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=wcK4AAAAIAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22thousands+of+Christians%22+ The slave trade of eastern Africa, Volume 1] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=wcK4AAAAIAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22thousands+of+Christians%22+ |date=20200821044412 }}. Barnes & Noble Books-Imports (1976) pp. 149-150, 158-159</ref>由於宗教法不允許基督徒參與貿易，因此穆斯林主宰了奴隸貿易，他們往會往越來越遠的地方尋找物資。<ref name=A2 />在集中管理的奧羅莫地區，如：吉貝山谷（Gibe Valley）和迪德薩（Didesa），農業和工業部門主要由奴隸勞動。奴隸勞動人口變得非常巨大，在吉貝地區（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gibe_region Gibe Region]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gibe_region |date=20200807144544 }}）、[[吉馬地區|吉馬地區]]、以前的吉拉王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gera Kingdom of Gera]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Gera |date=20200409005745 }}）和揚杰羅王國（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Janjero Kingdom of Janjero]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Janjero |date=20200221051146 }}）等地，奴隸人口佔總人口的三分之一到三分之二。<ref name=A22>W. G. Clarence-Smith [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA106#v=onepage&q=%22Slaves%20constituted%22&f=false The Economics of the Indian Ocean Slave Trade in the Nineteenth Centuryy] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=9Hfl5rpXM1sC&pg=PA106#v=onepage&q=%22Slaves%20constituted%22&f=false |date=20200821043955 }}. Psychology Press (1989) pp. 106 Google Books</ref><ref name=A23>International African Institute [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=xHtRAQAAIAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22slaves+of+both+sexes%22 Ethnographic Survey of Africa, Volume 5, Issue 2] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=xHtRAQAAIAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22slaves+of+both+sexes%22 |date=20200821042301 }}. (1969) pp. 31 Google Books</ref>

===當代衣索比亞的形成===
將奧羅莫人融入衣索比亞這個統一的國家過程的敘述有非常多種說法，<ref name="Sorenson2001p39">{{cite book|author1=Atsuko Karin Matsuoka|author2=John Sorenson|title=Ghosts and Shadows: Construction of Identity and Community in an African Diaspora|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gkk_hn3qF2sC&pg=PA39| year=2001|publisher= University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-8331-9|pages=39–41}}</ref>其中一個敘述是暴力且被強迫的。許多學者指出，在征服和創建現代衣索比亞南部領土的期間，一個名為「neftenya-gabbar」的系統殘酷地逼迫奧羅莫人服從，<ref name="Sorenson2001p39"/>[[孟尼利克二世|孟尼利克二世]]的軍隊對平民和戰士實施暴行，包括酷刑、大規模殺戮和大規模奴役，<ref name="ReferenceA">Mohammed Hassen, Conquest, Tyranny, and Ethnocide against the Oromo: A Historical Assessment of Human Rights Conditions in Ethiopia, ca. 1880s–2002 , Northeast African Studies Volume 9, Number 3, 2002 (New Series)</ref><ref>Mekuria Bulcha, Genocidal violence in the making of nation and state in Ethiopia, African Sociological Review</ref>還對迪齊人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dizi_people Dizi People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dizi_people |date=20170405161242 }}）和卡斐丘人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kafficho_people Kafficho People]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kafficho_people |date=20200813125325 }}）進行了大規模的暴行。<ref name="ReferenceB">Alemayehu Kumsa, Power and Powerlessness in Contemporary Ethiopia, Charles University in Prague</ref><ref>Haberland, "Amharic Manuscript", pp. 241f</ref>由於戰爭、飢荒和暴行造成南方人（奧羅莫人、迪齊人、卡斐丘人、山齊拉人（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanqella Shanqella]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanqella |date=20190629015936 }}））死亡人數估計達數百萬。<ref name="ReferenceA"/><ref name="ReferenceY">Alemayehu Kumsa, Power and Powerlessness in Contemporary Ethiopia, Charles University in Prague pp. 1122</ref><ref name="ReferenceZ">Eshete Gemeda, [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=aUcbtM9k_fgC&pg=PA186 African Egalitarian Values and Indigenous Genres: A Comparative Approach to the Functional and Contextual Studies of Oromo National Literature in a Contemporary Perspective] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=aUcbtM9k_fgC&pg=PA186 |date=20200821043055 }}, pp 186;<br>A. K. Bulatovich Ethiopia Through Russian Eyes: Country in Transition, 1896-1898, translated by Richard Seltzer, 2000 pp. 68</ref>

而其他敘述則不同意此說法，如：俄羅斯作家亞歷山大·布拉圖維奇（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Bulatovich Aleksandr Bulatovich]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Bulatovich |date=20160810171319 }}）在二十世紀初期前往衣索比亞，他表示，在[[吉馬|吉馬]]（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma Jimma]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jimma |date=20201126123925 }}）、勒卡（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lieka Leka]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lieka |date=20161228081302 }}）和韋勒加省（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Welega_Province Welega Province]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Welega_Province |date=20201105155848 }}）這樣的和平地區，先前的秩序得到保護，不會干涉他們的自治，而在戰後納入的地區，統治者也不會侵犯人民及其宗教信仰，以合法和公正對待他們。<ref name=D1>Aleksandr Ksaver'evich Bulatovich [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ Ethiopia Through Russian Eyes: Country in Transition, 1896-1898- Google Books"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ |date=20200821044011 }}: , 2000. p. 69.</ref><ref name=D1-1>Aleksandr Ksaver'evich Bulatovich [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ Ethiopia Through Russian Eyes: Country in Transition, 1896-1898- Google Books"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ |date=20200821044011 }}: , 2000. p. 68.</ref>他解釋，死亡是因為許多因素造成，如：飢荒和疾病，而蹂躪了衣索比亞這一時期的歷史。<ref name=D2>Aleksandr Ksaver'evich Bulatovich [https://www.google.com.et/search?tbm=bks&hl=en Ethiopia Through Russian Eyes: Country in Transition, 1896-1898- Google Books"]: , 2000. p. 11.</ref><ref name=D3>Aleksandr Ksaver'evich Bulatovich [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ Ethiopia Through Russian Eyes: Country in Transition, 1896-1898- Google Books"] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=W3hyAAAAMAAJ |date=20200821044011 }}: , 2000. p. 12.</ref><ref name=E1>Peter Gill [https://books.google.com.et/books?id=lzZpOyYE1DYC&pg=PT41 Famine and Foreigners: Ethiopia Since Live Aid] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.et/books?id=lzZpOyYE1DYC&pg=PT41 |date=20200821043656 }} Oxford University Press, 2010 Google Books</ref>

在一些敘述中提到，衣索比亞最大的兩個族群：奧羅莫人和[[]]之間的關係被稱為「阿比西尼亞封建殖民主義」（Abyssinian feudal colonialism）。
例如，根據歷史學家及作家梅庫莉雅·布夏（Mekuria Bulcha）的說法，奧羅莫人在20世紀前期就像歐洲殖民主義者一樣被[[安哈拉人|安哈拉人]]殖民。阿比西尼亞將軍拉斯·達格爾（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darge_Sahle_Selassie Ras Darge]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darge_Sahle_Selassie |date=20210205002255 }}）下令「摧毀[[阿爾西地區|阿爾西地區]]」（Arsi mutilation）。抵抗安哈拉人佔領的奧羅莫人受到截肢和毀容之對待，且村莊也被摧毀。到1901年，奧羅莫人居住的部分地區減少至原來人口的三分之一或一半。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bulcha|first1=Mekuria|title=Flight and Integration|publisher=Nordic Africa Institute|pages=39–40|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=YEf4SJbLFqYC&pg=PA40|accessdate=16 May 2017|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821052402/https://books.google.ca/books?id=YEf4SJbLFqYC&pg=PA40|dead-url=no}}</ref>根據阿克巴爾·艾哈邁德（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akbar_S._Ahmed Akbar Ahmad]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Akbar_S._Ahmed |date=20210126211206 }}）的說法，安哈拉語中「Saw naw Galla?」（是人類還是加拉？）都表示安哈拉人對奧羅莫人的蔑視。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Ahmad|first1=Akbar|title=The Thistle and the Drone|publisher=Brookings Institution Press|page=233|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=n_YMKlVfFLkC&pg=PA233|accessdate=16 May 2017|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821035400/https://books.google.ca/books?id=n_YMKlVfFLkC&pg=PA233|dead-url=no}}</ref>在1960年代出現了政治爭端，有報導闡述說，安哈拉的領導人對奧羅莫人的教育機會有歧視。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Mengisteab|first1=Kidane|title=State Building and Democratization in Africa|date=1999|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|page=240|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=ywXaX9eqt0IC&pg=PA240|accessdate=16 May 2017|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821042222/https://books.google.ca/books?id=ywXaX9eqt0IC&pg=PA240|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在另一方面，有些人則不同意殖民主義的論點。據包勒斯·謬起亞斯（Paulos Milkias）和格塔丘·梅塔斐力亞（Getachew Metaferia）介紹，安哈拉人和奧羅莫人都有著相同的地理和歷史空間；兩者在文化、經濟和政治上相互交織；數百萬人從兩個群體追溯他們自身的起源；奧羅莫菁英份子是地區的要角，如[[貢德爾|貢德爾]]和西瓦（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa Shewa]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shewa |date=20210131165348 }}）等地；安哈拉人和奧羅莫統治精英之間的交往極為廣泛。數以千計的安哈拉人，從貴族到農民，從教育到文盲，忠實地服從奧羅莫部長和將軍，包勒斯和格塔丘說道，「就像有成千上萬的英國人，無論貴族或平民都忠實地服務於英國的非洲血統的部長和將軍」。所有的一切與安哈拉人殖民奧羅莫人的論點不一致，在殖民地制度下既不會發生也不可能發生。<ref name=A1-2-1-1>Paulos Milkias, Getachew Metaferia [https://books.google.com/books?id=pq1MBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA274 The Battle of Adwa: Reflections on Ethiopia's Historic Victory Against European Colonialism]. Algora Publishing (2005) pp. 274-275 Google Books</ref>據一些學者說，奧羅莫人成為衣索比亞貴族的一部分，而卻不失去他們的身份。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd/cstdy:@field(DOCID+et0020) |title=Ethiopian Oroo nobility |publisher=Lcweb2.loc.gov |date= |accessdate=2017-05-16 |archive-date=2013-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318004527/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd%2Fcstdy%3A%40field%28DOCID+et0020%29 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=MenelikA11>Fikre Tolossa [http://www.ethiopianreview.com/index/33633 Nobles of Oromo Descent Who Ruled Ethiopia] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ethiopianreview.com/index/33633 |date=20160603082640 }}. Ethiopian Review (1992)</ref><ref name=MenelikA20>Harold D. Nelson, Irving Kaplan [https://books.google.com/books?id=t_JyAAAAMAAJ Ethiopia, a Country Study, Volume 28]. American University, Foreign Area Studies (1981) pp. 14 Google Books</ref>其他學者則指出，在安哈拉人統治期間，奧羅莫人的邊緣化導致許多人將他們的名字與安哈拉人融合。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Trevor|first1=Paul|title=Being and Becoming Oromo: Historical and Anthropological Enquiries|publisher=Nordic Africa Isntitute|page=32|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=xmp2lsKlqx0C&pg=PA32&lpg=PA32|accessdate=16 May 2017|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821054521/https://books.google.ca/books?id=xmp2lsKlqx0C&pg=PA32&lpg=PA32|dead-url=no}}</ref>

據和約翰·索倫森（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_L._Sorenson John Sorenson]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_L._Sorenson |date=20201112021448 }}）介紹，在十九世紀和二十世紀時，對於奧羅莫農民進行了大規模的殘酷剝削。但實際情況更為複雜，因為一些奧羅莫人越過族裔界線，與阿比西尼亞部隊合作。這個時期奧羅莫人在衣索比亞軍隊中佔有重要地位，且皇室成員中部有奧羅莫血統。<ref name="Sorenson2001p41">{{cite book|author1=Atsuko Karin Matsuoka|author2=John Sorenson|title=Ghosts and Shadows: Construction of Identity and Community in an African Diaspora|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gkk_hn3qF2sC&pg=PA39| year=2001|publisher= University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-8331-9|pages=40–42}}</ref><ref name=MenelikA3>Chris Prouty [https://books.google.com/books?id=8bItAQAAIAAJ Empress Taytu and Menilek II: Ethiopia, 1883-1910]. Ravens Educational & Development Services (1986) pp. 25 Google Books</ref><ref name=MenelikA5>Chris Prouty [https://books.google.com/books?id=8bItAQAAIAAJ Empress Taytu and Menilek II: Ethiopia, 1883-1910]. Ravens Educational & Development Services (1986) pp. 156 & 157 Google Books</ref>例如，伊亞蘇五世（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iyasu_V Iyasu V]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iyasu_V |date=20201108173214 }}）是衣索比亞指派但未被加冕的皇帝（1913-1916年），而海爾·塞拉西一世（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haile_Selassie Haile Selassie I]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haile_Selassie |date=20210130092944 }}）則是1930年至1974年衣索比亞被加冕且公認的皇帝。<ref name="Tronvoll">Kjetil Tronvoll, ''Ethiopia, a new start?'', (Minority Rights Group: 2000)</ref>其他的奧羅莫人也在這時期的衣索比亞獲得較高的職位。<ref name="Woodward">Peter Woodward, ''Conflict and peace in the Horn of Africa: federalism and its alternatives'', (Dartmouth Pub. Co.: 1994), p.29.</ref><ref>Haile Selassie I, ''My Life and Ethiopia's Progress: The Autobiography of Emperor Haile Sellassie I'', translated from Amharic by Edward Ullendorff. (New York: Frontline Books, 1999), vol. 1 p. 13</ref>

奧羅莫傳統主義者指出，那些爬到有權力地位的人，透過拒絕自身奧羅莫文化，而採用其他文化來使他們晉升高位。<ref>{{cite book|author1=Atsuko Karin Matsuoka|author2=John Sorenson|title=Ghosts and Shadows: Construction of Identity and Community in an African Diaspora|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gkk_hn3qF2sC&pg=PA39| year=2001|publisher= University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-8331-9|pages=45–46}}</ref>部分衣索比亞人認為，奧羅莫人是國家的一部分，但另一部份則認為，奧羅莫人有一個漫長的、被貶損的歷史，被安哈拉人等民族以「原始野蠻人」來對待，奧羅莫人需要「復興奧羅莫文化與歷史」。<ref>{{cite book|author1=Atsuko Karin Matsuoka|author2=John Sorenson|title=Ghosts and Shadows: Construction of Identity and Community in an African Diaspora|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=gkk_hn3qF2sC&pg=PA39| year=2001|publisher= University of Toronto Press|isbn=978-0-8020-8331-9|pages=40–47}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=Paul Trevor William Baxter|author2=Jan Hultin|author3=Alessandro Triulzi|title=Being and Becoming Oromo: Historical and Anthropological Enquiries |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xmp2lsKlqx0C&pg=PA71 |year=1996|publisher=Nordic Africa Institute|isbn=978-91-7106-379-3|pages=71–75}}</ref>

==社會、家庭與婚姻==
===家庭===
奧羅莫家庭的基本單位是父系（男性）大家庭，鄰里和社區是與大家庭相連的重要社交網絡。男人是家庭中的主管，對妻子（或妻子們）和未婚子女有掌管他們的權力。典型的奧羅莫男人有一個妻子，但由於伊斯蘭教和其他文化的影響，部分奧羅莫男人與一個以上的妻子結婚（一夫多妻）。在奧羅莫社會，離婚的行為不被鼓勵。而現今，奧羅莫婦女已經開始抗拒一夫多妻制。<ref name="#1">[http://www.everyculture.com/wc/Costa-Rica-to-Georgia/Oromos.html] {{Wayback|url=http://www.everyculture.com/wc/Costa-Rica-to-Georgia/Oromos.html |date=20191117102946 }}，FAMILY LIFE</ref>

由於父權制和性別歧視，奧羅莫婦女被視為劣於男子，沒有權力。奧羅莫婦女生活在三重壓迫下：階級、性別和種族壓迫。在外來殖民之前，奧羅莫婦女有一個名為「siqqee」的機構來幫助他們反對男性統治和壓迫。雖然解放鬥爭中有奧羅莫婦女戰士和軍事領導者，但奧羅莫婦女的地位卻仍沒有甚麼改變。<ref name="#1"/>

===加達制度===
加達制度（[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gadaa Gadaa System]{{Wayback|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gadaa |date=20201112013641 }}）是衣索比亞的奧羅莫人所使用的一種傳統管理體制，經由世代累績的社群經驗所形成。人們透過該體制規範社群內的政治、經濟、社會，以及宗教活動，或用來處理紛爭、補償的問題，以及保障女性的權益。加達可說是一種規範道德、凝聚社會，以及表現社區文化的機制。加達體制下的社群共分為五個階級，其中一個階級會作為領導階層，內部有主席、官員等職位以及一個議會。每一個階級都必須經歷一系列的層級發展，最後才能成為領導階層，並每隔八年交棒給下一個階級。階級只有男性可以加入，他們的父親也都是階級成員。不過，男人們在做決策時也會諮詢女性的意見，以保障女性的權益。階級的制度會由社群內的史學家口頭傳授，內容涵蓋了歷史、法律、儀式、計時法、宇宙學、神話、行為準則，以及加達體制的功用等知識。集會和儀式通常會在西克莫無花果樹（Sycamore Tree）底下進行，而部分地區的大型部落則是會建造儀式專用的空間和加達中心。而加達體制相關的知識也會透過家庭與學校傳承給孩子。<ref name="#2">{{Cite web |url=http://twh.boch.gov.tw/non_material/intro.aspx?id=406 |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2017-05-01 |archive-date=2019-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130014417/https://twh.boch.gov.tw/non_material/intro.aspx?id=406 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

